<setup>
  <function name="f">e^x</function>
  <derivative name="fP">$f</derivative>
  <function name="g" styleNumber="3">ln(x)</function>
  <derivative name="gP">$g</derivative>

  <label name="flabel" anchor="(2.25,9.5)"><m>y=f(x)</m></label>
  <label name="glabel" anchor="(9.25, 3.65)"><m>y=g(x)</m></label>
  
  <number name="a0">0</number>
  <number name="a1">1</number>
  <number name="a2">2</number>
  <number name="a3">3</number>
  <number name="a4">4</number>

  <number name="b1">0</number>
  <number name="b2">ln(2)</number>
  <number name="b3">ln(3)</number>
  <number name="b4">ln(4)</number>
  
  <number name="p">2</number>
  <number name="q">4</number>
  <number name="r">8</number> 
  

  
</setup>

<p>
  Consider the functions <m>f(x) = e^x</m> and <m>g(x) = \ln(x)</m>.
</p>  

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        To begin, state the derivatives of <m>f(x)</m> and <m>g(x)</m>, respectively. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>f'(x) = </m><answer><award>$fP</award></answer>
      </p>  
      <p>
        <m>g'(x) = </m><answer><award>$gP</award></answer>
      </p> 
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        Complete the following table of function and derivative values for <m>g(x) = \ln(x)</m>.
      </p>

      
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell halign="right"><m>x</m>:</cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>$a1</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>$a2</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>$a3</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>$a4</m></cell>
        </row>  
        <row>
          <cell halign="right"><m>g(x)</m>:</cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>\ln($a1)</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$g($a2)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$g($a3)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$g($a4)</award></answer></cell>
        </row> 
        <row>
          <cell halign="right"><m>g'(x)</m>:</cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>1</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$gP($a2)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$gP($a3)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$gP($a4)</award></answer></cell>
        </row> 
      </tabular>        

    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        Complete the following table of function and derivative values for <m>f(x) = e^x</m>.
      </p>

      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell halign="right"><m>x</m>:</cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>\ln(1)</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>\ln(2)</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>\ln(3)</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>\ln(4)</m></cell>
        </row>  
        <row>
          <cell halign="right"><m>f(x)</m>:</cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>1</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$f($b2)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$f($b3)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$f($b4)</award></answer></cell>
        </row> 
        <row>
          <cell halign="right"><m>f'(x)</m>:</cell>
          <cell halign="center"><m>1</m></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$fP($b2)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$fP($b3)</award></answer></cell>
          <cell halign="center"><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award>$$fP($b4)</award></answer></cell>
        </row> 
      </tabular>       
      


    </li>     
    <li>
      <p>
        One of the important facts about the function <m>f(x) = e^x</m> that is hightlighted by our work above is that at any point <m>(a,b)</m> on the graph of <m>f(x) = e^x</m>, the <em>slope</em> of the tangent line to <m>f(x) = e^x</m> is <answer>
                <choiceInput inline>
                  <choice>?</choice>
                  <choice>the reciprocal of</choice>
                  <choice credit="1">equal to</choice>
                  <choice>the opposite of</choice>
                </choiceInput>  
              </answer> the <em>value</em> of <m>f(x) = e^x</m> at that point.  
      </p>  
    </li>  
  </ol>

</p>  
